Domain: x>0, x≠1. Put t = log_2 x (so x = 2^t, t≠0). Converting to base 2 gives log_4 x = t/2, log_x 16 = 4/t, log_x 8 = 3/t. Substituting into the equation yields
t/2 - 4/t = 7/6 - 3/t ⇒ t/2 - 1/t = 7/6.
Multiplying by 6t gives 3t^2 - 7t - 6 = 0, whose roots are t = 3 and t = −2/3. Thus x = 2^t = 8 or x = 2^{-2/3}, both of which satisfy the original equation.

\boxed{\{8,\;2^{-2/3}\}}

Final answer: \{8,\;2^{-2/3}\}
